<title>NORWAY: Kvaerner, ABB in Peru power plant deal.</title>
<headline>Kvaerner, ABB in Peru power plant deal.</headline>
<dateline>OSLO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Anglo-Norwegian construction and engineering group Kvaerner ASA said on Friday its energy and hydropower divisions, together with ABB Power Generation Inc in Denver, the United States, had won a 370 million crown contract to build a power station in Peru.</p>
<p>Kvaerner's slice of the contract is 160 million crowns, according to a statement on the Oslo bourse.  </p>
<p>Kvaerner said its Kvaerner Energy unit in Norway and Kvaerner Hydropower Inc in San Fransisco were involved in the deal for the power station at Canon del Pato.</p>
<p>The equipment is to be delivered between mid-1998 and mid-1999.</p>
